Claims Claims I/We Claim 1. An autonomous convertible cooking device (100), wherein the device (100) comprises: a platform (103) with grooves (116) for accommodating the gantry (112) and pan structure (105); a cylindrical container (104) to store the batter; a pushing means (106) to discharge the batter atop of the pan (102) for cooking; a heating pan structure (105) mounted on a platform (103) through the grooves (116) provided on its sides for heating the batter; a gantry (112) with a slider (110) provisioned to deliver three way sliding of the container (104) and the slider (110); a C-shaped arm (108) to carry out the cooked batter as a roll by sliding through the grooves (114) on the platform; an input/output device for a user to access the autonomous cooking device, and to enter preferences, type of dish to be prepared, quantity of dish to be cooked based on number of persons or equivalent calories the person(s) wish to take; at least one level and weight sensor; at least one communication device; and at least one electronic controlling device, capable of reading a preference from the user(s) from a preset listing, quantities, cooking times and conditions, determining a quantity in the storage using the level and/or weight sensors, comparing the quantity with a prescribed contentment quantity, and display them based on the comparisons on the output device and on the preferred communication device over a communication network. 2. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the device is so configured to make south Indian delicacies dosa and idly simultaneously. 3. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the batter is prepared and placed in the cylindrical container (104) by dismantling the pushing means with push bar/rod setup (106) for preparing dosa before starting the device (100). 4. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the batter inside the container (104) is dispensed uniformly with the push bar (106) on to the pan (102), after receiving the instructions by the user regarding the quantity of units/dosaâs to be made. 5. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the uniform dispensing of the batter is made possible through the three way sliding of the cylindrical container (104) with the aid of gantry (112) and slider (110) attached to the container on the grooves of device platform (103). 6. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the heating of the pan (102) is carried out by the steamer/heater unit under the pan structure (105) with controlled intensity of the heating, responsive to temperature required for preparing the recipe. 7. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the finished unit/dosa is rolled from the pan (102) with the C-shaped arm (108) by sliding over the grooves (114) on the sides of the cooking platform (103) and returns to its position before making another unit/dosa throughout the cooking process. 8. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the pan structure (105) is detachable from the grooves (116) of the platform (103) for converting the device for making idly whenever desired by the user. 9. The device (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the autonomous convertible cooking device (100) is equipped with weight sensors for measuring ingredient levels in the storage means for the food being prepared. 10. The autonomous convertible cooking device (200) according to claim 1, wherein the idly setup (200) of the device comprises: a plurality of pallets (220) with hollow circular impressions (221) on them to collect dispensed batter; a stacker (222) for stacking the pallets (220) dispensed with batter for cooking/heating and 

 a steamer/heating unit (224) within the stacker (222) for heating the pallets (220) ; 11. The device (200) with idly setup as claimed in claim 9, wherein the batter is uniformly dispensed according to the userâ s instruction onto the pallets (220) with the aid of gantry (212) and slider (210) through the grooves (216) on the platform (203) and gantry grooves (218) similar to the three way sliding according to claim 4. 12. The device (200) as claimed in claim 9, wherein the batter dispensed pallets (220) are conveyed through the grooves (216) of the platform (203) into the stacker (222) and are placed on top of one another. 13. The device (200) as claimed in claim 9, wherein the stacker (222) cooks idly by heating the pallets (220) with the steamer setup (224) inside of it. 14. The device (200) as claimed in claim 9, wherein the device operates with an alternate current source connected to mains. 15. The device (200) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the electronic controlling device performs a health check of the device and holds the device in its idle state until a command for cooking is received. 16. The device (200) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the communications over a network is through home wireless internet connectivity or by a WiFI/GSM based internet connectivity. 17. The device (200) as claimed in claim 1, wherein the device is for making idly, dosaâs and the like. 18. A method of operating an autonomous cooking device over a communication network and cooking desired quantities of idly or dosa, wherein the method comprises steps of: placing, the batter inside the cylindrical container (104) of the unit; 

 uniform dispensing of required amount of batter onto the pan (102) or pallets (220) for making dosa or idly respectively; allowing a user to connect remotely to the cooking device with use of the userâs communication device connected to an electronic controller of the device; inputting preferences to make desired quantity of units/dosa or idly based on number of persons or based on equivalent calories they wish to take; and the electronic controlling device, capable of reading the preference from the user from a preset listing, quantities, cooking times and conditions, also determines a quantity in the storage using a plurality of level and/or weight sensors. IB
